artwork.abstract: Impression, Sunrise (French: Impression, soleil levant) is a painting by Claude Monet first shown at what would become known as the 'Exhibition of the Impressionists' in Paris in April, 1874. The painting is credited with inspiring the name of the Impressionist movement. \nImpression, Sunrise depicts the port of Le Havre, Monet's hometown. Painting in the style of Claude Monet.  

A hazy, yellow-orange sunrise illuminates the harbor of a French port city, with a silhouette of a ship in the foreground and a series of masts and buildings in the background
